title: Republican Graham raised $1.05 million in third quarter
text:
Republican Graham raised $1.05 million in third quarter WASHINGTON U.S. Republican presidential candidate and U.S. Senator Lindsey Graham takes the stage to speak at the No Labels Problem Solver Convention in Manchester, New Hampshire October 12, 2015. Reuters/Brian Snyder 
WASHINGTON U.S. Republican presidential candidate Lindsey Graham raised $1.05 million in the latest quarter, his campaign said on Thursday. 
The South Carolina senator spent almost $2 million in the third quarter and has nearly $1.7 million cash on hand, the campaign said.
